20
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:44,800
the Beach Boys, or C, the Beatles? I think most people would say the answer is C, the Beatles.

21
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:50,320
Okay, we'll find out the answer later in the programme. Now throwing diamonds in the sky might

22
00:01:50,319 --> 00:01:56,559
sound crazy, but it's far from the wildest idea scientists have thought up to decarbonise the planet.

23
00:01:56,559 --> 00:02:02,479
Oceans hold 16 times more carbon than the Earth's atmosphere, and could hold even more.

24
00:02:02,479 --> 00:02:08,400
If the fish and plankton living there had more available nutrients, food that animals and plants

25
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:15,039
need to grow. But how to provide these nutrients? Believe it or not, one answer involves, you guessed it,

26
00:02:15,039 --> 00:02:21,359
whale poo. David King chairs the Centre for Climate Repair at Cambridge University.

27
00:02:21,359 --> 00:02:27,199
He explained how his unusual idea would work to BBC World Service programme Discovery.

28
00:02:28,959 --> 00:02:34,719
Imagine now a pod of whales all coming up and pooing in the same area of the ocean.

29
00:02:35,439 --> 00:02:41,039
This could be in an eddy current, and it could lead to something like 10,000 to 20,000 square

30
00:02:41,039 --> 00:02:48,159
kilometres being covered in nutrients, including iron. And as we know from observations today,

31
00:02:48,159 --> 00:02:52,079
within three months that region is chock-a-block with fish.

32
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:59,280
Whales live in groups called pods. They swim up to the ocean surface to poo, and this poo can

33
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:05,919
be spread in an eddy, a large current of water moving in a circular motion, like a giant whirlpool.

34
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:12,079
As a result, huge areas of the ocean are covered in nutrients and become chock-a-block with fish,

35
00:03:12,639 --> 00:03:19,759
an informal way to say full of fish. Another original idea being explored is rock weathering.

36
00:03:19,759 --> 00:03:24,560
Carbon is slowly locked into rocks and mountains over thousands of years by natural

37
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:31,439
geological processes. This literally groundbreaking idea would speed up the process by locking

38
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:35,039
carbon into rocks that have been dug up through industrial mining.

39
