43
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:11,760
that's really good because it creates a circular economy. Mining for diamonds creates tons of waste

44
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:19,280
rock, which could be used to capture carbon. Professor James wants to repurpose this rock to find a new

45
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:26,160
use for it. Not only would this lock more carbon, it also creates a circular economy, an economic

46
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:32,960
model which involves sharing, reusing, and recycling products for as long as possible to avoid waste

47
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:38,960
and to reduce levels of carbon. While these ideas might sound strange, they're all theoretically

48
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:45,440
possible, and looking to science for positive solutions reminds some people of the early ecological

49
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:52,000
movement which started in the 1960s, and now 50 years later is being taken seriously.

50
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:56,480
Speaking of the 1960s, it's time to reveal the answer to my question, Sam.

51
